The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the grand opening of the AFWERX facility in Las Vegas. He thanked Secretary Heather Wilson for her leadership and praised the men and women in uniform for their service. Pence emphasized the importance of innovation and creativity in maintaining a strong military and highlighted the investments made by the Trump administration in military spending. He described AFWERX Vegas as an incubator for new ideas and a catalyst for new technologies, with a focus on breaking down barriers and streamlining processes to ensure that innovative solutions can be quickly implemented. Pence expressed his belief that the work done at AFWERX Vegas will contribute to a stronger and safer America, and he thanked all those in attendance for their commitment to the nation's defense.